caption: Delicious food, extremely efficient and friendly service!! Will come back again!!

My friend and I had lunch there on 3/28 and absolutely loved the place. The food was very fresh and delicious. Service was prompt, excellent, warm and welcoming as well as the restaurant being spotlessly clean.  My friend served two tours of duty in Vietnam and stated this restaurant was better and more authentic than any food he had during his service in Vietnam.  Who cares if it is Chinese-owned (which was a ridiculous criticism by another customer) - here the chef is Vietnamese.  We highly recommend Miss Saigon and will try to get there often.  They deserve five stars.

We had a great lunch here. Hot and sour soup full of fresh vegetables in a flavourful, not too spicy broth. Spring rolls were delicate and crisp, grilled shrimp skewers were juicy, perfectly charred. Chicken banh mi was tender and full of flavour—i loved the tangy mayonnaise! Service was exceptionally attentive. We will be back!
Very nice and cozy place with excellent food and service. We will come back with more people.
The service and food are great!
The food is fresh and delicious, and the customer service is excellent!

The good, the bad and the dangerous: We ordered number of dishes from here this evening.  We were enjoying them until I decided to try the grilled chicken soup my daughter was eating.  I selected a piece of the grilled chicken to try and as I bit into it something cut my gums.  At first I thought it might be a piece of bone, but when placed on a paper towel and examined, it proved to be a staple.  A staple.  See image.  The gentleman on the phone was very apologetic but I can only wonder what would have happened had it been swallowed.  Clearly not safe.

You can call and order via phone super easily. The food comes real fast. The food is very fresh and warm: summer roll’s rice paper was very thin, shrimp with veggies warmed and delicious. Some people might think this is not authentic. I can’t say but I love Vietnamese food and this was really good. Highly recommend. We will order again.
Really disappointing banh mi. Bread was soggy. No spice at all. I didn’t like the pork very much. Just not good. 2 stars because delivery was fast and the iced coffee was pretty good.

Disclaimer I am not Vietnamese so I am not reviewing their authenticity but rather taste, speed for pickup and service! I ordered the bean curd lunch special and it was delicious. 9$ and ready for pick-up in 5 minutes. I waited outside and the nice cashier brought it outside to me so quickly. Would recommend to anyone in the neighborhood!

Came here because we were craving Vietnamese food and unfortunately this did not satisfy us at all. It's Chinese owned and I can tell that this wasn't authentic Vietnamese food. Banh mi had no pate and was served with potato chipa. The favors were all off (lemongrass pork had no lemongrass).
